description_translated:
Ms. N. Thi Ngoan is 45 years old, Ms 01030004. She is a very hard working woman. She has a shop repairing mopeds and her husband is a barber. She has 2 children who are also employed, and thus her family's income is quite stable at 12 USD per day. She and her group have gone through 2 loan cycles and have repaid the loans. She likes this loan program because it allows her to repay gradually, and at the same time allowing her to save extra cash to assist her children. For this loan cycle, she wishes to borrow 280 USD to buy spare parts to sell and to use in her repair shop. In her group, there are the following members:

Ms. Dang Thi N., Ms 01030001, loan amount 280 USD to invest in her business of selling and repairing telephones;
Ms. Le Thi Quy, Ms 01030003, loan amount 280 USD to invest in her shop selling breakfast food;
Ms. Dang Thi Ngoc T., Ms 01030005, loan amount 280 USD to buy supplies for repairing calculators;
Ms. N. Thi Hoa, Ms 01030035, loan amount 280 USD to invest in her refreshment shop





<br /><p><strong>Translated from Vietnamese by Thu Ostrander, Kiva Volunteer</strong></p>
